# Intuit Design System - FontWeight Token Library

## Primitive FontWeight Tokens (DO NOT USE DIRECTLY IN PLUGINS)

- `--font-weight-100`: 100
- `--font-weight-200`: 200
- `--font-weight-300`: 300
- `--font-weight-400`: 400
- `--font-weight-500`: 500
- `--font-weight-600`: 600
- `--font-weight-700`: 700
- `--font-weight-800`: 800
- `--font-weight-900`: 900

## Semantic FontWeight Tokens (USE THESE IN PLUGINS)

### Weight
- `--font-weight-body`: --font-weight-400 /* For body text styles (paragraph text). Do not use these in atom sized UI components instead use font-component tokens. */
- `--font-weight-body-bold`: --font-weight-600 /* For inline bolding, emphasis or adding visual hierarchy to body text styles (paragraph text) */
- `--font-weight-body-semibold`: --font-weight-500 /* Optional weight for adding emphasis or visual hierarchy to body text styles (paragraph text) */
- `--font-weight-component`: --font-weight-400 /* For component text styles */
- `--font-weight-component-bold`: --font-weight-600 /* For inline bolding, emphasis, or adding visual hierarchy to component text styles */
- `--font-weight-component-semibold`: --font-weight-500 /* Optional weight for adding emphasis or visual hierarchy to component text styles */
- `--font-weight-display`: --font-weight-500 /* For display text styles */
- `--font-weight-display-bold`: --font-weight-500 /* For inline bolding of display text styles */
- `--font-weight-heading`: --font-weight-500 /* For heading text styles */
- `--font-weight-heading-bold`: --font-weight-500 /* For inline bolding of heading text styles */
- `--font-weight-input-label`: --font-weight-400 /* For input label text styles */
- `--font-weight-input-text`: --font-weight-400 /* For input text styles */
- `--font-weight-mega`: --font-weight-400 /* For mega text styles */
- `--font-weight-mega-bold`: --font-weight-500 /* For inline bolding of mega text styles */
